	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A 27-year-old man is expected to appear in the Centane Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday in connection with the murder of a man who had been missing, Eastern Cape police said on Sunday. A 37-year-old man got lost on Friday night at Manzana in Qina village, Centane, said Captain Jackson Manatha. "The deceased was found on Saturday...at about 09:30. He had an upper body injury." Following a police investigation, the suspect, aged 27, was arrested. He is now due in the Centane Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday. "The motive for the murder is not known." 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  